TikTok Data Report

Sampling

  1. Explore political TikTok (ask people from community)
  2. Create a list of around ~100 accounts and manually label by ideology
  3. Create a list of political hashtags (~150 hashtags)
  4. Sample TikToks that mentioned political hashtags (~33k TikToks)
  5. Create a list of accounts that mentioned political hashtags (~1000 TikTokers)
  6. Label all accounts by ideology and content
  • In total: 965 accounts identified as either right or left leaning
  1. Get all TikToks from 965 political accounts
  • In total: ~228k TikToks

Mentions network

Graph shows mention network of TikTok users (mentions often happen when people duet each other). When a right-leaning TikToker mentions another right-leaning TikToker the line is red. For intra left-leaning connection its blue. Mentions across party lines are purple.

In the lower-right cluster there is a conservative TikToker @nickvideos who is being piled on by a lot of liberal TikTokers
